## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="3e869-103">将 <xref:System.SerializableAttribute> 特性应用于某个类型，以指示此类型的实例可以被序列化。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3e869-103">Apply the <xref:System.SerializableAttribute> attribute to a type to indicate that instances of this type can be serialized.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="3e869-104">如果要序列化的<xref:System.Runtime.Serialization.SerializationException>对象图中的任何类型都没有应用该<xref:System.SerializableAttribute>属性, 则公共语言运行时将引发。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3e869-104">The common language runtime throws <xref:System.Runtime.Serialization.SerializationException> if any type in the graph of objects being serialized does not have the <xref:System.SerializableAttribute> attribute applied.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="3e869-105">即使该类还实现了<xref:System.Runtime.Serialization.ISerializable>用于控制序列化过程的接口, 也应用特性。<xref:System.SerializableAttribute></span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3e869-105">Apply the <xref:System.SerializableAttribute> attribute even if the class also implements the <xref:System.Runtime.Serialization.ISerializable> interface to control the serialization process.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="3e869-106">将<xref:System.SerializableAttribute>特性应用于某个类型时, 默认情况下将序列化所有私有字段和公共字段。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3e869-106">When you apply the <xref:System.SerializableAttribute> attribute to a type, all private and public fields are serialized by default.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="3e869-107">可以通过实现<xref:System.Runtime.Serialization.ISerializable>接口来重写序列化过程, 从而更精确地控制序列化。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3e869-107">You can control serialization more granularly by implementing the <xref:System.Runtime.Serialization.ISerializable> interface to override the serialization process.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="3e869-108">或者, 您可以通过将<xref:System.NonSerializedAttribute>特性应用于字段, 从序列化中排除字段。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3e869-108">Or you can exclude fields from serialization by applying the <xref:System.NonSerializedAttribute> attribute to the field.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="3e869-109">如果可序列化的类型的字段包含指针、句柄或其他特定于特定环境的数据结构, 并且在其他环境中无法有意义地重建, 则你可能需要应用<xref:System.NonSerializedAttribute>属性到该字段。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3e869-109">If a field of a serializable type contains a pointer, a handle, or some other data structure that is specific to a particular environment, and cannot be meaningfully reconstituted in a different environment, then you might want to apply the <xref:System.NonSerializedAttribute> attribute to that field.</span></span>  
  
